Equation of tangent $x+t^2 y=2 c t \Rightarrow T \equiv(2 c t, 0)$ and $\mathrm{T}^{\prime} \equiv\left(0, \frac{2 c}{t}\right)$ Equation of normal $\mathrm{t}^3 \mathrm{x}-\mathrm{ty}=\mathrm{c}\left(\mathrm{t}^4-1\right) ; \mathrm{N} \equiv\left[\mathrm{c}\left(\mathrm{t}-\frac{1}{\mathrm{t}^3}\right), 0\right] ; \mathrm{N} \equiv\left[0, c\left(\frac{1}{\mathrm{t}}-\mathrm{t}^3\right)\right]$
$\begin{aligned}
& \Rightarrow N T=\frac{\mathrm{c}}{\mathrm{t}^3}+\mathrm{ct} ; \mathrm{N}^{\prime} \mathrm{T}^{\prime}=\mathrm{ct}^3+\frac{\mathrm{c}}{\mathrm{t}} \\
& \Rightarrow \Delta=\frac{1}{2}\left|\frac{\mathrm{c}}{\mathrm{t}^3}+\mathrm{ct}\right| \frac{\mathrm{c}}{\mathrm{t}} \Rightarrow \frac{1}{\Delta}=\frac{2 \mathrm{t}^4}{\mathrm{c}^2\left(1+\mathrm{t}^4\right)} \text { and } \Delta^{\prime}=\frac{1}{2}\left|\mathrm{ct}^3+\frac{\mathrm{c}}{\mathrm{t}}\right| \mathrm{ct} \\
& \Rightarrow \frac{1}{\Delta^{\prime}}=\frac{2}{\mathrm{c}^2\left(1+\mathrm{t}^4\right)} \Rightarrow \frac{1}{\Delta}+\frac{1}{\Delta^{\prime}}=\frac{2}{\mathrm{c}^2}
\end{aligned}$
